JOHANNESBURG - New details regarding President Jacob Zuma's latest cabinet reshuffle have been revealed by the Sunday Times.
	
	The reshuffle saw former State Security Minister David Mahlobo moved to the energy department. READ: Zuma breaking world records with 11 cabinet reshuffles: Kasrils A top level Russian team reportedly met with Zuma shortly before he announced the cabinet changes. The team was allegedly acting on direct orders of Russian President Vladimir Putin and included members of the military, police and intelligence.  Journalist Qaanitah Hunter says Mahlobo had gone to Russia with a presidential aid before his appointment. eNCA